<center> Pendragon Society</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ualethiaorceloria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alethia or Celoria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/2/02 10:38:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3598.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If your on a raid shouldn't the guild / group being buying the dots and not the clerics?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You would think so wouldn't you? But this isn't always the case. I have walked away from raids where I have gotten jack for dots spent cost. You get a promise at the start that you will be reimbursed but sometimes that just never happens.<br>
<br>
As for being broke. Yeah my Cleric is probably one of the most broke Clerics on the server. lol I don't normally sell the things I win in randoms in groups (I have like 12 or so twinks all suited up lmao or I give the stuff to friends) so no money for me is garnered that way.. Not ALL high lvl dungeons have the gem drop rate that OS has. I prefer Chardok to OS for XP because to be frank the XP in OS sucks arse compared to Chardok.  I don't charge people for their rezzes ever and 8 out of 10 times I'll hit the cancel button in a trade window when I'm offered it (the other 2 times would be if I didn't like you/you caused me or my friends to die or I was so pressed for cash I really <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> needed</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that donation). I also do a lot of tradeskilling with my Cleric (bout all she's good for nowadays anyway cept rezzing) so that takes PP away as well.<br>
<br>
I keep 3 full stacks of dots on Cel at all times unless I haven't been able to get around to restocking despite the fact I rarely have money. Dots cost 210 a stack for me with 108cha and ally faction in Neriak but not every cleric can get them for this price, especially if they are pressed for time and are forced to buy dots in a place like Thurgadin where even with the highest faction they try and gouge you if you don't have a high cha. I have ended up with 2pp after a restock once but I sucked it up and I got by. No, I don't cast symbol on all party members when I XP as I feel only those that will gain agro the most, puller/MA/enchie/Bard, actually need it. Hell, I don't even symbol myself. I try and &quot;cut costs&quot; as it were as much as possible without detriment to the group and a party member that I would not normally symbol is more than welcome to give me dots, or 10pp for the cost of one, to do so and I'll happily oblige.<br>
<br>
This is all through the eyes of a 56 Cleric who has performed this way since she first started having to buy dots for her symbols so take it for what its worth. I've only once been so strapped for pp that I couldn't fully restock my dots once. I don't earn 1.5k a night of XPing with Cel, when I do XP with her, because I don't let my group blindly give me all the gems/cash loot that drop and I don't always XP in high dollar zones. From my own standpoint I get by and usually have the cash to fund my reagents. I can see though how other clerics would be strapped for cash. It's all relative to the person.<br>
<br>
I suggest, if your in a group and wanting symbol that the Cleric isn't just automatically casting on you, that you ask said Cleric in an unoffensive way &quot;If its not too much trouble could I get a symbol please?&quot; 9 out of 10 times they will do so or at the very least tell you why they haven't/won't. Never be afraid to ask. <p><div align=center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=343243"><img src="http://www.ulujain.org/albums/album04/abe.jpg" border=0></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=351766"><img src="http://www.ulujain.org/albums/album04/abf.jpg" border=0></a><br><a href="mailto:alethia_tamire@yahoo.com"><font size=-2>EMAIL</a></font></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraelven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raelven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Priestess of Moo</span><br>  Posts: 950<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/2/02 10:39:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3598.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> BYO reagents. I always carry peridots, pearls, coffins, and keep another stash in the bank. Carry a stack of jasper or whatever with you and never be buffless again. <p><a href="http://www.saraquael.com">
